<div id="module-1" class="module-section active"><div class="module-header"><h2>Foundations of Integration</h2><div class="lectures">Lectures 1–2</div><a class="outline-link" href="../study_outline.md#module-1-foundations-of-integration" target="_blank">📖 Review in Study Outline &rarr;</a></div><div class="module-subtitle">No labeled exercises in this module. Work through the worked examples in the study outline.</div></div>
<div id="module-2" class="module-section "><div class="module-header"><h2>Advanced Integration Techniques</h2><div class="lectures">Lectures 6–9</div><a class="outline-link" href="../study_outline.md#module-2-advanced-integration-techniques" target="_blank">📖 Review in Study Outline &rarr;</a></div>
<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L8-1</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 8)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-2-advanced-integration-techniques" target="_blank">trig-substitution</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-2-advanced-integration-techniques" target="_blank">completing-square</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">Evaluate $ \displaystyle\int \frac{x}{\sqrt{x^{2} + x + 1}} \,dx $</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 8 Example: ∫ x/√(3-2x-x²) dx (completing square + trig sub)</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L8-1">\int \frac{x}{\sqrt{x^{2} + x + 1}} \;dx</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L8-1')" id="btn-L8-1">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>

<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L8-2</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 8)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-2-advanced-integration-techniques" target="_blank">arc-length</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-2-advanced-integration-techniques" target="_blank">trig-substitution</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">Find the length of the arc of $ y = \frac{1}{2}x^{2} $ from $ P(-1,\frac{1}{2}) $ to $ Q(1,\frac{1}{2}) $.</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 4 Example: arc length of y²=x³ from (1,1) to (4,8)</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L8-2">y = \frac{1}{2} x^{2},\quad P(-1,\tfrac{1}{2}),\ Q(1,\tfrac{1}{2})</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L8-2')" id="btn-L8-2">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>

<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L9-1</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 9)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-2-advanced-integration-techniques" target="_blank">partial-fractions</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-2-advanced-integration-techniques" target="_blank">distinct-linear</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">Evaluate $ \displaystyle\int \frac{dx}{x^{2} - a^{2}} $, where $ a \neq 0 $.</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 9 Example: ∫ (x+5)/(x²+x-2) dx (distinct linear factors)</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L9-1">\int \frac{dx}{x^{2} - a^{2}},\qquad a \neq 0</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L9-1')" id="btn-L9-1">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>

<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L9-2</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 9)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-2-advanced-integration-techniques" target="_blank">partial-fractions</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-2-advanced-integration-techniques" target="_blank">repeated-linear</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">Evaluate $ \displaystyle\int \frac{x^{2} + 1}{(x-3)(x-2)^{2}} \,dx $.</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 9 Example: ∫ (x⁴-2x²+4x+1)/(x³-x²-x+1) dx (repeated linear)</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L9-2">\int \frac{x^{2} + 1}{(x-3)(x-2)^{2}} \;dx</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L9-2')" id="btn-L9-2">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>

<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L9-3</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 9)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-2-advanced-integration-techniques" target="_blank">rationalizing-substitution</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">Evaluate $ \displaystyle\int_{0}^{1} \frac{dx}{2\sqrt{x + 3} + x} $.</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 9 Example: ∫ √(x+4)/x dx (rationalizing sub u = √(x+4))</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L9-3">\int_{0}^{1} \frac{dx}{2\sqrt{x + 3} + x}</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L9-3')" id="btn-L9-3">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>
</div>
<div id="module-3" class="module-section "><div class="module-header"><h2>Applications of Integration</h2><div class="lectures">Lectures 4–5</div><a class="outline-link" href="../study_outline.md#module-3-applications-of-integration" target="_blank">📖 Review in Study Outline &rarr;</a></div>
<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L4-1</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 4)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-3-applications-of-integration" target="_blank">arc-length</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">Find the length of the arc of the curve $ y = \frac{1}{2}x^{2} $ from $ P(-1,\frac{1}{2}) $ to $ Q(1,\frac{1}{2}) $.</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 4 Example: y²=x³ from (1,1) to (4,8); y²=x from (0,0) to (1,1)</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L4-1">y = \frac{1}{2} x^{2},\quad P(-1,\tfrac{1}{2}),\ Q(1,\tfrac{1}{2})</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L4-1')" id="btn-L4-1">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>

<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L5-1</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 5)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-3-applications-of-integration" target="_blank">surface-of-revolution</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-3-applications-of-integration" target="_blank">rotation-about-x-axis</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">Find the area of the surface obtained by rotating $ x = 1 + 2y^{2},\ 1 \le y \le 2 $, about the $ x $-axis.</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 5 Example: y=√(4-x²) rotated about x-axis; y=eˣ rotated about x-axis</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L5-1">x = 1 + 2y^{2},\quad 1 \le y \le 2,\quad \text{about }x\text{-axis}</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L5-1')" id="btn-L5-1">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>

<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L5-2</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 5)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-3-applications-of-integration" target="_blank">surface-of-revolution</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-3-applications-of-integration" target="_blank">rotation-about-x-axis</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">Find the area of the surface obtained by rotating $ 9x = y^{2} + 18,\ 2 \le x \le 6 $, about the $ x $-axis.</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 5 Example: y=√(4-x²) rotated about x-axis; y=eˣ rotated about x-axis</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L5-2">9x = y^{2} + 18,\quad 2 \le x \le 6,\quad \text{about }x\text{-axis}</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L5-2')" id="btn-L5-2">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>
</div>
<div id="module-4" class="module-section "><div class="module-header"><h2>Numerical Integration</h2><div class="lectures">Lectures 10–11</div><a class="outline-link" href="../study_outline.md#module-4-numerical-integration" target="_blank">📖 Review in Study Outline &rarr;</a></div><div class="module-subtitle">No labeled exercises in this module. Work through the worked examples in the study outline.</div></div>
<div id="module-5" class="module-section "><div class="module-header"><h2>Polar Coordinates & Parametric Curves</h2><div class="lectures">Lectures 12–13</div><a class="outline-link" href="../study_outline.md#module-5-polar-coordinates-parametric-curves" target="_blank">📖 Review in Study Outline &rarr;</a></div>
<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L12-1</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 12)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-5-polar-coordinates-parametric-curves" target="_blank">polar-coordinates</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-5-polar-coordinates-parametric-curves" target="_blank">tangents</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-5-polar-coordinates-parametric-curves" target="_blank">horizontal-vertical-tangents</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">Find the points on the curve $ r = 1 - \sin\theta $ where the tangent line is horizontal or vertical.</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 12 Example: r=1+sinθ — find slope at θ=π/3; find horizontal/vertical tangents</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L12-1">r = 1 - \sin\theta</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L12-1')" id="btn-L12-1">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>
</div>
<div id="module-6" class="module-section "><div class="module-header"><h2>Improper Integrals</h2><div class="lectures">Lectures 14</div><a class="outline-link" href="../study_outline.md#module-6-improper-integrals" target="_blank">📖 Review in Study Outline &rarr;</a></div><div class="module-subtitle">No labeled exercises in this module. Work through the worked examples in the study outline.</div></div>
<div id="module-7" class="module-section "><div class="module-header"><h2>Infinite Sequences & Series</h2><div class="lectures">Lectures 15–18</div><a class="outline-link" href="../study_outline.md#module-7-infinite-sequences-series" target="_blank">📖 Review in Study Outline &rarr;</a></div>
<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L16-1</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 16)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-7-infinite-sequences-series" target="_blank">series-convergence</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-7-infinite-sequences-series" target="_blank">telescoping</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-7-infinite-sequences-series" target="_blank">partial-fractions</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">Determine whether $ \displaystyle\sum_{n=2}^{\infty} \frac{1}{n^{2} - 1} $ converges or diverges. If convergent, find its sum.</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 16 Example: ∑ 1/(n(n+1)) — telescoping via partial fractions</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L16-1">\sum_{n=2}^{\infty} \frac{1}{n^{2} - 1}</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L16-1')" id="btn-L16-1">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>

<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L16-2</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 16)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-7-infinite-sequences-series" target="_blank">geometric-series</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-7-infinite-sequences-series" target="_blank">radius-of-convergence</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">Find the values of $ x $ for which $ \displaystyle\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} (-5)^{n} x^{n} $ converges. Find the sum for those $ x $.</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 16 Example: ∑ 2^{2n} 3^{1-n} — geometric series convergence</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L16-2">\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} (-5)^{n} x^{n}</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L16-2')" id="btn-L16-2">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>

<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L16-3</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 16)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-7-infinite-sequences-series" target="_blank">partial-sums</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-7-infinite-sequences-series" target="_blank">series-sum</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">If the $ n $th partial sum is $ s_{n} = 3 - n\,2^{-n} $, find $ a_{n} $ and $ \displaystyle\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} a_{n} $.</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 16 Example: s_n = 2n/(3n+5), find ∑ a_n</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L16-3">s_{n} = 3 - n\,2^{-n}</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L16-3')" id="btn-L16-3">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>

<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L16-4</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 16)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-7-infinite-sequences-series" target="_blank">series-divergence</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-7-infinite-sequences-series" target="_blank">telescoping</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-7-infinite-sequences-series" target="_blank">divergence-test</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">Show that $ \displaystyle\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \ln\!\left(1 + \frac{1}{n}\right) $ diverges even though its terms approach 0.</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 16 Example: harmonic series ∑ 1/n diverges despite terms → 0</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L16-4">\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \ln\!\left(1 + \frac{1}{n}\right)</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L16-4')" id="btn-L16-4">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>

<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L18-1</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 18)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-7-infinite-sequences-series" target="_blank">alternating-series</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-7-infinite-sequences-series" target="_blank">absolute-convergence</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-7-infinite-sequences-series" target="_blank">conditional-convergence</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">Determine whether $ \displaystyle\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} (-1)^{n-1} \frac{n}{n^{2} + 4} $ is absolutely convergent, conditionally convergent, or divergent.</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 18 Examples: ∑ (-1)^{n-1}/n² (abs conv), ∑ (-1)^n/n (cond conv), ∑ (-1)^{n+1} n²/(n³+1)</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L18-1">\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} (-1)^{n-1} \frac{n}{n^{2} + 4}</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L18-1')" id="btn-L18-1">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>
</div>
<div id="module-8" class="module-section "><div class="module-header"><h2>Power Series, Taylor Series & Applications</h2><div class="lectures">Lectures 19–22</div><a class="outline-link" href="../study_outline.md#module-8-power-series-taylor-series-applications" target="_blank">📖 Review in Study Outline &rarr;</a></div>
<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L19-1</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 19)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-8-power-series-taylor-series-applications" target="_blank">power-series</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-8-power-series-taylor-series-applications" target="_blank">radius-of-convergence</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-8-power-series-taylor-series-applications" target="_blank">interval-of-convergence</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">Find the radius of convergence and interval of convergence of $ \displaystyle\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} \frac{n(x+2)^{n}}{3^{n+1}} $.</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 19 Example: ∑ (-3)^n x^n/√(n+1) — find R and interval</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L19-1">\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} \frac{n(x+2)^{n}}{3^{n+1}}</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L19-1')" id="btn-L19-1">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>

<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L20-1</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 20)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-8-power-series-taylor-series-applications" target="_blank">power-series</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-8-power-series-taylor-series-applications" target="_blank">geometric-series</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">Find a power series representation for $ \dfrac{1}{x+2} $.</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 20 Example: express 1/(1+x²) as power series</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L20-1">\frac{1}{x+2}</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L20-1')" id="btn-L20-1">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>

<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L20-2abc</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 20)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-8-power-series-taylor-series-applications" target="_blank">power-series</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-8-power-series-taylor-series-applications" target="_blank">differentiation</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-8-power-series-taylor-series-applications" target="_blank">sum-of-series</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">(a) From $ \sum x^{n} $, find $ \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} n x^{n-1} $. (b) Find $ \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \frac{n}{2^{n}} $. (c) Find $ \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \frac{n^{2}}{2^{n}} $.</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 20 Example: express 1/(1-x)² via differentiation</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L20-2abc">\sum_{n=1}^{\infty} n x^{n-1},\quad \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \frac{n}{2^{n}},\quad \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \frac{n^{2}}{2^{n}}</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L20-2abc')" id="btn-L20-2abc">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>

<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L20-3</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 20)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-8-power-series-taylor-series-applications" target="_blank">power-series</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-8-power-series-taylor-series-applications" target="_blank">integration</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-8-power-series-taylor-series-applications" target="_blank">approximation</a></div>
</div>
<div class="exercise-body">
<div class="exercise-problem">Use a power series to approximate $ \displaystyle\int_{0}^{0.1} x \arctan(3x) \,dx $ correct to within $ 10^{-7} $.</div>
<div class="exercise-similar">📌 Similar examples: Lecture 20 Example: ∫ 1/(1+x⁷) as power series, approximate to 10⁻⁷</div>
<div class="codebox">
<pre id="latex-L20-3">\int_{0}^{0.1} x \arctan(3x) \,dx</pre>
<button onclick="copyLaTeX('L20-3')" id="btn-L20-3">Copy LaTeX</button>
</div>
</div></div>

<div class="exercise">
<div class="exercise-header">
<div><span class="exercise-id">Exercise L22-1</span> <span class="exercise-lecture">(Lecture 22)</span></div>
<div class="exercise-tags"><a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-8-power-series-taylor-series-applications" target="_blank">maclaurin-series</a> <a class="tag" href="../study_outline.md#module-8-power-series-taylor-series-applications" target="_blank">trigonometric-identities</a></div>
</div>
